overed.\n7. Advice to avoid syntax errors: \n   - Always ensure the sensitivity list is `always @(*)` for combinational logic.\n   - Match port names exactly as specified in the input spec.\n   - Ensure all signals are declared as `logic`.\n   - When using case statements, cover all possible input combinations or provide a default case to avoid latch inference.",
